is fired at a target 10,000,000 kilometers away it will gradually<br>
expand with increasing distance .It will resemble a flak burst  only when there  some dust or something around to scatter the light. Otherwise a laser beam is invisible in space.<br>
The flak burst especial effect occurrs solely because goerge<br>
lucas made no special effort to reconcile his special effects<br>
with the laws of physics.<br>
High energy particle beam beam weapons can be seen in space because they are made of luminous plasma gas<br>
which emmitts light  and other ems  from its excited electrons.<br>
<br>
<br>
2. High explosive and nuclear warheads create glowing fireballs<br>
of expanding plasma gas when they detonate..<br>
<br>
3. There is a way to deliver a gigaton or more of energy <br>
to a target in a space battle other then a nuclear or a chemical explosive. The answer is to use a kkv (kinetic kill vehicle). If for example a missile fires a 1000 kilogram warhead<br>
at 5 km/sec from a starship that is moving at a large fraction<br>
of light velocity, or if an artillary piece like a cannon does<br>
this then the kinetic energy of the projectile can be calculated by the kinetic energy formula in physics.<br>
The velocity of the projectile or kkv is the sum of the ships velocity + the velocity imparted by the projectiles launch.<br>
Example 5 km/sec + 150,000 km/sec is 150,005 km/sec<br>
: Kinetic energy then equals 1000 kg * 150,000,500 meters<br>
per second sqaured/ 2 * y ( the relatavistic  gamma factor).<br>
= 1.1 * 10 to the 16 power joules * 1000 which equals<br>
1.1 * 10 to the 19 power joules. This is the about the  amount of energy   that would released by a 1 gigaton Thermonuclear  explosion.<br>
Tim<br>
